The paper deals with automated understanding of linear perspective in landscape photography, which involves image processing and computer vision techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also addresses the problem of on-site feedback for photo composition, which falls under the category of cs.GR (Graphics). The proposed method involves contour detection, which is a common technique in multimedia processing, suggesting the category cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses image retrieval, which is a subfield of information retrieval, indicating the category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper proposes a novel vanishing point detection method that exploits global structures in the scene, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, suggesting the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
